  54. ‌val warning_attribute: ?ppwarning:bool -> Parsetree.attribute -> unit
  55.   (** Apply warning settings from the specified attribute.
  56.       "ocaml.warning"/"ocaml.warnerror" (and variants without the prefix)
  57.       are processed and other attributes are ignored.

  59.       Also implement ocaml.ppwarning (unless ~ppwarning:false is
  60.       passed).
  61.   *)

  63. ‌val warning_scope:
  64.   ?ppwarning:bool ->
  65.   Parsetree.attributes -> (unit -> 'a) -> 'a
  66.   (** Execute a function in a new scope for warning settings.  This
  67.       means that the effect of any call to [warning_attribute] during
  68.       the execution of this function will be discarded after
  69.       execution.

  71.       The function also takes a list of attributes which are processed
  72.       with [warning_attribute] in the fresh scope before the function
  73.       is executed.
  74.   *)
